The paper deals with the task of de-identification of medical records using machine learning techniques. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses privacy-preserving techniques for sharing medical data, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of adversarial learning techniques for generating privacy-preserving text representations is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for de-identification, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR).
